# Session start

1. Read `HANDOFF.md` first — check **Priority C — COMPLETE** (lane closed; active work is Priority A)
2. Read `docs/ideas/FINAL-PHASE-PLAN.md` — active Priority A item
3. Read `PLATFORM-GUIDE.md` (rules, modules, launch checklist)
4. Read `README.md` sections only when needed
5. Work on one module per session
6. State which build-priority item the task serves (A, B, D, or E — not C unless operator reopens)

# Before each action

Consult `HANDOFF.md`, then `docs/ideas/FINAL-PHASE-PLAN.md`, then `PLATFORM-GUIDE.md`, then `README.md` sections when needed.

# After each action

**Non-negotiable:** after every completed action:

1. Update `HANDOFF.md` **Live session state**
2. Update `AGENTS.md` so operator sync, MVP at a glance, and completion records match HANDOFF
3. Append `README.md` Ordered Build Record when routes, modules, or behavior changed

Read README **sections** only — not the whole file every time — see `PLATFORM-GUIDE.md` Completion standard.

# Session end

1. Run `npm run lint && npm run type-check && npm run test`
2. Commit and push to GitHub
3. Update `HANDOFF.md` live session state and session log
4. Update `AGENTS.md` if live state or project story changed
5. Append `README.md` Ordered Build Record if behavior changed

# Handoff rule

Never switch between Cursor and Codex with uncommitted work. Update `HANDOFF.md` first.
